# OAuth client credentials for the Google Drive, OneDrive, and Dropbox
# backends.  Copy this file to `.env` (gitignored) and fill in the values from
# your OAuth app registrations before building.
#
# These serve two purposes:
#
#  1. BUILD TIME - the build scripts source `.env`, and the values are baked
#     into the binary (via `env!` / `option_env!`).  This is how the official
#     builds ship a working OAuth app.
#
#  2. RUNTIME (override / escape hatch) - the same variable names are also read
#     from the process environment at runtime and, when set (non-empty),
#     override the baked-in values.  So an end user (or a delegate) can point
#     the tool at THEIR OWN OAuth app - no rebuild needed - by exporting the
#     variable before launching.  The backup data lives in the user's own cloud
#     account, so a fresh app with read scope reaches the same backups.  This is
#     the wind-down protection for the three OAuth backends: if the project's
#     OAuth apps ever stop working, users are not locked out.
#
# OneDrive uses the public-client flow, so it has no secret (only CLIENT_ID).

GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=
DROPBOX_APP_KEY=
DROPBOX_APP_SECRET=
ONEDRIVE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
